        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`Bash(find:*)` treats `find` as a read-only permission, but unrestricted `find` can execute or mutate through options such as `-exec`, `-execdir`, and `-delete`. This becomes a guardrail bypass because an allow entry like this would permit commands such as `find . -exec git commit ... \\;` even though those utilities remain forbidden elsewhere. Do not add a blanket `find:*` allow; restrict it to a non-executing wrapper or specific safe forms.",
              "severity": "P0",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/verify/orchestra.rs",
              "line": 105,
              "category": "security"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:0be98bfde5d51d1cb818fae04a02c023a00249a091fa614fabb5ada1fe72b365",
          "at": "2026-04-22T23:04:37Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "zero_findings",
          "findings": [],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:9e2d99851f1ca8b3e3f361268e449db023a77f901f27757b5054dcd1edd66d51",
          "at": "2026-04-22T23:14:12Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`Bash(sort:*)` is being allowed on the premise that `sort` is exec-incapable, but GNU sort supports `--compress-program=PROG`, which executes an arbitrary compression helper while creating temporary files. That gives this allow entry the same class of wrapper-exec bypass the change is explicitly trying to keep forbidden for `find` and `env`, so a user with this permission can route execution through `sort` instead of the blocked command names.",
              "severity": "P0",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/verify/orchestra.rs",
              "line": 106,
              "category": "security"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:9e2d99851f1ca8b3e3f361268e449db023a77f901f27757b5054dcd1edd66d51",
          "at": "2026-04-22T23:15:52Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`Bash(sort:*)` is being added to the allowed baseline as \"exec-incapable\", but GNU `sort` can execute an arbitrary helper via `--compress-program=PROG` when it creates temporary files. That means an allowed `sort` invocation can wrap forbidden commands in the same class as `env`/`find -exec`, bypassing the `FORBIDDEN_ALLOW` guardrail. Keep `sort` forbidden unless the permission can exclude `--compress-program`.",
              "severity": "P0",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/verify/orchestra.rs",
              "line": 106,
              "category": "security"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:9e2d99851f1ca8b3e3f361268e449db023a77f901f27757b5054dcd1edd66d51",
          "at": "2026-04-22T23:16:44Z"
