            {
              "message": "`.claude/rules/10-guardrails.md` now says `Bash(env:*)` was moved to `allow`, but this round’s policy explicitly keeps `env` forbidden because it is used by the wrap-execute boundary. That makes the rules text disagree with `.claude/settings.json` and the intended guardrail, and could mislead future permission updates.",
